Macadamia (almond) nut SALMON! 🔥
.
Thanks to amazing SIL/bestie for this unreal recipe @valenejadan 🙏🏻❤️🥰😍
.
I made this recipe at the same time as the macadamia nut chicken. There’s plenty of sauce for both chicken and salmon! 
.
Season 2-3 Salmon with Old Bay Seasoning or any seasoning to your liking
1/4 cup of macadamia nuts chopped (I use almonds)
3 cups of panko breadcrumbs
1/4 cup of flour
1/2 cup of milk
2 whole eggs

Step 1: Mix almonds and Panko in a bowl
Step 2: Mix milk and eggs in another bowl
Step 3: Lay flour out by itself separate in another bowl

Step 4: Cover salmon with the flour
Step 5: Dip into egg mix
Step 6: Dip and cover Salmon very well in the Panko
Step 7: Fry both sides till brown

Sauce: Ingredients
1 pint heavy cream
1/4 cup soy sauce
2 tablespoon corn starch
2 tablespoon water

Step 1: Mix corn starch and water in a bowl
Step 2: Mix heavy cream and soy sauce in sauce pan
Step 3: Add the corn starch mix in little by little to thicken sauce
Step 4: Bring to a boil on high stirring occasionally and then back to low to keep warm until ready to eat!!
.
.
Mashed potatoes ingredients:
🥔 Potatoes 
🥛 Heavy whipping cream
🥛 Milk
🧈 Butter
🧄 Garlic salt
🧄 Garlic powder
🍃 Chives
.
.
Enjoy☺️
.
.
.

Macadamia (Almond) Nut Chicken 
.
Thanks to amazing SIL/bestie for this 🔥🔥🔥🔥 recipe!!! So amazing!!!!!!! 
.
Chicken: Ingredients
Season 6-8 chicken breasts with salt and pepper to liking
1/4 cup of macadamia nuts chopped (I use almonds)
3 cups of panko breadcrumbs
1/4 cup of flour
1/2 cup of milk
2 whole eggs

Step 1: Mix almonds and Panko in a bowl
Step 2: Mix milk and eggs in another bowl
Step 3: Lay flour out by itself separate in another bowl

Step 4: Cover chicken with the flour
Step 5: Dip into egg mix
Step 6: Dip and cover chicken very well in the Panko
Step 7: Fry both sides till brown
Step 8: Stick into the oven on 350 for 12 minutes
While that’s cooking...

Sauce: Ingredients
1 pint heavy cream
1/4 cup soy sauce
2 tablespoon corn starch
2 tablespoon water

Step 1: Mix corn starch and water in a bowl
Step 2: Mix heavy cream and soy sauce in sauce pan
Step 3: Add the corn starch mix in little by little to thicken sauce
Step 4: Bring to a boil on high stirring occasionally and then back to low to keep warm until ready to eat!!
.
Mashed potatoes ingredients:
🥔 Potatoes 
🥛 Heavy whipping cream
🥛 Milk
🧈 Butter
🧄 Garlic salt
🧄 Garlic powder
🍃 Chives
.
.
Enjoy☺️
.
.
.

Mac N Cheese made by 💁🏽‍♀️ Recipe by my SIL @revareev 
.
.
Land o lakes sells a brick of yellow American cheese (aka government cheese) argue with yo mama this is the best cheese ever lol use this! Shred or just cut into pieces.  They sell it at the Arabic store.
Or use any cheese you like but plz freshly shred it pre shred cheese is a huge buzz kill to this fresh recipe.
😂😂💜🙏🏽
salt the pasta water but when you drain the noodles save  2 cups of the pasta water! 
.
Also when you drain your pasta and it cools down a little break an egg into the noodles and coat them all before you add cheese mixture to them!
I would start the noodles after you’ve competed the Béchamel. 
.
 To make your bechamel keep your heat on the lowest setting and melt a stick of butter. Once melted take 2 table spoons of flour and whisk. Keep whisking until you create thick almost paste. Be sure not
To use high heat or brown the butter.  While you keep whisking add in a cup of milk or heavy cream if you really want the ultimate flavor.
Add seasons and keep whisking 
 teaspoon ground mustard 
Teaspoon garlic powder
Little less than a Teaspoon onion powder 
Lots of white pepper (I love pepper you can use black pepper also) 
Paprika (when Mac is done I add a little more paprika on top) 
.
.
Add cheese (if you don’t get the land o lakes cheese and just use other kinds (that you shred yourself
😝
) Use half a stick of velveeta cheese along with it! 
.
Add half a brick of cream cheese 
.
Continue to whisk on low heat making sure the cheese you added doesn’t stick to bottom of pot! Now this is where you will decide how much of the pasta water to use. 
Mac & cheese dries up pretty quick so more is better than less.
.

My husband asked who’s making pacha… I decided to go for it! He told me to call my mom because I couldn’t do it by myself! 😂 Don’t challenge me hunny!🙂 I WILL be doing this for the holidays and I can’t wait to do it again! I truly enjoyed it! 
.
Recipe
📝 Cleaning the Pacha (tripe)
📌Use the spine of a knife to clean, scraping off the extra fat. I personally liked using scissors more and getting deeper into the pieces. Then cut into the size you want, usually medium to large. If some pieces are small, it’s okay!  Kids eat the small pacha and they love that it’s their personal pacha. I got mine from @restaurantdepot_official 
📍Then clean and soak twice. 
📌In a big bowl
📍One cup flour
📍Two tablespoons vinegar 
📍Two tablespoons Rose water 
📍 1-2 cups of lemon juice 
📍Two tablespoons Himalayan salt
📍Two cups of water
📌 Soak for half hour and wash very well. Repeat soaking with new mixture 👆🏻
📌After the second pacha soaking, wash each one inside and out very good. 
📍Sew all of it except an inch and a half. Give yourself enough room to fill with meat and rice mixture.
.
📝Dab dry if you have extra or want to use it for a different time. Put in freezer ziplock bag 
.
📝Mixture
We did for 43 pacha’s 
📍3 1/2 cups rice 
📍2 large onions
📍1 garlic 
📍5 cups cubed cut up meat 
📍3 to 4 tablespoons baherat
📍3 tablespoons salt 
📍1 tablespoons black pepper
📍4 tablespoons oil
.
📝Wash rice and meat separately
Drain water out 
👩🏻‍🍳 Mix all the ingredients & start stuffing! 
📝Buy big needles from Joann, Michael’s or Walmart. Thick thread 🧵 This time I did @walmart plastic needles and WOW I loved it so much more! Flexible and easier to work with on pacha!
📝After filling, sew the rest of the pacha. 
📝 Use neck bones , oxtails, or any kind of meat with bones. I put them into the pressure cooker for 1 hour with water and salt! You will add this broth into the pot of pacha later on🥰
📝 Cook for 3 hours add bay leaves to your broth! Last hour add your chickpeas and onions!
.
I love adding raw onions and squeeze fresh lemon juice!! WOWW! 🔥🔥 Hits the spot every holiday! I hope you guys enjoy this video!!!
.
.
